      "content": "i mean, if we're talking about 'complexities,' shouldn't we admit that a foreign policy that triggers a power vacuum and allows groups like ISIS to move in is just objectively a bad strategy? like, even if the intention was good, can we really call a policy 'successful' if it basically creates more terrorists?",
